<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Introduction to Astronomy</title>
    <script src="https://unpkg.com/htmx.org@1.9.0"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Introduction to Astronomy</h1>

    <p>Explore the wonders of the night sky and our place in the cosmos.</p>

    <h2>The Solar System</h2>

    <div hx-get="/api/planets" hx-trigger="load">
        <p>Our solar system consists of eight planets orbiting the Sun:</p>

        <ul>
            <li><strong>Mercury</strong>: Smallest planet, closest to the Sun</li>
            <li><strong>Venus</strong>: Hottest planet due to greenhouse effect</li>
            <li><strong>Earth</strong>: The only known planet with liquid water on its surface</li>
            <li><strong>Mars</strong>: The Red Planet, target of many exploration missions</li>
            <li><strong>Jupiter</strong>: Largest planet, famous for its Great Red Spot</li>
            <li><strong>Saturn</strong>: Known for its spectacular ring system</li>
            <li><strong>Uranus</strong>: Rotates on its side, unique among planets</li>
            <li><strong>Neptune</strong>: Windiest planet with storms reaching 1,200 mph</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>Celestial Navigation Chart</h2>

    <img src="../../images/api-flow.jpg" alt="Star Chart Reference">

    <h2>Observing Tips</h2>

    <div hx-get="/api/conditions" hx-trigger="revealed">
        <h3>Best Viewing Conditions</h3>
        <p>For optimal stargazing experience:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Find a location away from city lights (dark sky sites)</li>
            <li>Allow 20-30 minutes for your eyes to adapt to darkness</li>
            <li>Check the moon phase - new moon provides darkest skies</li>
            <li>Use red flashlights to preserve night vision</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Seasonal Highlights</h3>
        <p>Each season offers unique celestial events:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Spring</strong>: Leo constellation, galaxies in Virgo cluster</li>
            <li><strong>Summer</strong>: Milky Way at its brightest, Perseid meteor shower</li>
            <li><strong>Autumn</strong>: Andromeda Galaxy visible to naked eye</li>
            <li><strong>Winter</strong>: Orion constellation, brightest stars of the year</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
